libsysactivity
------------------------------------------
A lightweight library that retrieves statistics of the system's activity in a
portable and thread safe way. In each OS that it supports it offers the same
API for retrieving the activity of: hard disks, CPUs, memory, processes and
network interfaces.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libgcc1-4.9.2-3
  libsysactivity1-0.7.0+git20120521-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-1
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.18.0.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://libsysactivity.sf.net/

Canonical download:
  git://libsysactivity.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/libsysactivity/libsysactivity

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsysactivity-0.7.0+git20120521-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsysactivity-0.7.0+git20120521-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsysactivity-0.7.0+git20120521-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsysactivity-0.7.0+git20120521-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsysactivity1-0.7.0+git20120521-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsysactivity-devel-0.7.0+git20120521-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsysactivity)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsysactivity.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsysactivity/COPYING
